  <body>
    <h1>How to make Water Toast</h1>

 
   
<p> A common recipe from the early 1900's, water toast is not really an appealing meal, but stands to show human creativity with the means available to them
     
  
  <details> 
     <summary>Ingredients</summary>
    <section>
      <ol>
        <li>2 slices dry toast</li>
        <li>3/4 tsp. of salt</li>
        <li>1 cup of boiling water</li>
        <li>1/2 tbsp. of butter</li>
     
      </ol>
    </section>
    </details>
 
    <section>
      <ol>
        <li> toast bread (via toaster, grill, etc.) </li>
        <li> boil the cup of water and add in salt, place boiling salt water in seperate dish </li>
        <li> dunk each piece individually in the hot water dish until sufficiently soaked </li>
        <li> spread butter on toast </li>
        <li> serve immediatly, realize making water toast was a bad idea and dispose immediately. </li>
    
    
  
